The paper deals with language model pre-training and its application to natural language processing tasks such as question answering. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with the intersection of computer science and linguistics. The paper also involves information retrieval (IR) techniques, which suggests cs.IR as a likely sub-category. The use of neural networks and deep learning methods points towards cs.LG (Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.DL (Machine Learning) as possible sub-categories.
